<module>
    <h>i</h>
    <p><g>i</g>
        <en>she, her</en> is the feminine singular (third person) <a href="?xx=nouns/personal_pronouns">personal
            pronoun</a>.</p>

    <section>
        <h>verbs</h>
        <section id="verbs-sbj">
            <h>subject</h>
            <!--<p><g>i</g> can be used as the subject of a verb.</p>-->
            <p>Examples with the predicative verb <g href="?gd=bi">bi</g>
                <en>be</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha Màiri sgìth. Tha i sgìth ag obair anns an achadh.</gd>
                        <tr>Mary is tired.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 7</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha Màiri bhàn anns an achadh an diugh agus tha <m>i</m> ag obair gu
                            trang.</gd>
                        <tr>Fair-headed Mary is in the field today and she is working busily.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 9</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>A bheil Seònaid anns an sgoil an diugh? Chan eil. Càit a bheil <m>i</m>?
                            Tha <m>i</m> anns an taigh.</gd>
                        <tr>Is Janet in the school today. No, she isn’t. Where is she? She is in the
                            house.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 14</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Càit a bheil a’ chaileag? Tha i anns an taigh. Dé tha i a’ dèanamh? Tha
                            i a’ cluich. Càit a bheil i a’ cluich? Tha i a’ cluich air an làr.</gd>
                        <tr>Where is the girl? She is in the house. What is she doing? She is
                            playing. Where is she playing? She is playing on the floor.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 15</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>


